82f4b9e9-45f1-4101-b37d-1f02d2226283	Morpho	The universal decentralized lending network providing open, permissionless infrastructure for overcollateralized crypto lending and borrowing on EVM chains.	Morpho is a decentralized lending protocol that has evolved from an optimization layer on top of Aave and Compound into a standalone, permissionless lending infrastructure (Morpho Blue) deployed on Ethereum, Base, and other EVM chains. The protocol enables the creation of isolated, immutable lending markets defined by customizable parameters (collateral asset, loan asset, liquidation ratio, oracle, and interest rate model), while Morpho Vaults allow third-party curators to manage risk and allocate capital across multiple markets for passive yield. With over $10B in cumulative deposits, Morpho has become the second-largest DeFi lending protocol behind Aave.\n\nMorpho's core smart contract is remarkably minimal at only 650 lines of Solidity code and has undergone extensive auditing. The protocol serves as backend infrastructure for major enterprises including Coinbase (powering its crypto-backed loans with over $1B in loan originations and $1.4B+ in cbBTC collateral). In February 2026, Apollo Global Management signed a cooperation agreement with the Morpho Association to acquire up to 90 million MORPHO tokens (9% of supply) over 48 months. The protocol is governed by the MORPHO token (max supply 1B) and operated through the Morpho Association, a French non-profit. Morpho Labs, the core development entity headquartered in Paris, was founded by four students from elite French engineering schools in 2021.	Crypto / Web3	Infrastructure	Liquid Token	Seed (Oct 2021): $1.35M. Series A (Jul 2022): $18M led by a16z and Variant, with participation from Nascent, Semantic Ventures, Cherry Ventures, Mechanism Capital, Spark Capital, Standard Crypto, Coinbase Ventures, and 80+ institutional/individual investors. Private round (Feb 2024): Undisclosed amount from Pantera Capital. Strategic round (Aug 2024): $50M led by Ribbit Capital, with a16z crypto, Coinbase Ventures, Variant Fund, Pantera Capital, Brevan Howard, BlockTower Capital, Kraken Ventures, Hack VC, IOSG, RockawayX, L1D, Mirana Ventures, Cherry Crypto, Semantic, Fenbushi Capital, LeadBlock Partners, Robot Ventures, and 40+ others. Total raised: ~$69-74M. Additionally, in February 2026, Apollo Global Management signed a cooperation agreement to acquire up to 90M MORPHO tokens (9% of total supply) over 48 months.	Morpho's primary competitors are Aave (the market leader with multi-chain dominance), Compound (the original pooled lending pioneer), and Euler (modular lending). Morpho differentiates through its minimalist base layer (650 lines of code), its permissionless market creation model, its curator-driven vault system, and its positioning as enterprise-grade infrastructure rather than a consumer-facing lending app. Coinbase's integration to power its crypto-backed loans is a major competitive moat. The Apollo partnership and Ethereum Foundation deposits further validate Morpho's institutional positioning.		discovered	{DeFi,Lending,Ethereum,Infrastructure,"Institutional DeFi","Liquid Token"}	\N	2026-03-25 06:26:00.789249	https://morpho.org	https://github.com/morpho-org	https://x.com/MorphoLabs	https://www.linkedin.com/company/morpho-labs	1e9bf641-c93c-4629-906a-f50db9050164	Lending/Borrowing	0	\N	\N	[{"title":"Morpho Blue Whitepaper","url":"https://resources.cryptocompare.com/asset-management/17952/1732199021661.pdf","source":"Morpho Labs (hosted on CryptoCompare)","relevance":"The foundational technical whitepaper detailing Morpho Blue's immutable, governance-minimized lending primitive design, isolated market architecture, oracle-agnostic pricing, and the trust model investors must understand before evaluating the protocol's security assumptions and competitive differentiation."},{"title":"Galaxy Research: The State of Crypto Lending","url":"https://assets.ctfassets.net/h62aj7eo1csj/4vkA9567QmK4pyYoPBtrQa/fb039fd97d657d8151dcf4d3e969e481/The_State_of_Crypto_Lending_-_Galaxy_Research.pdf","source":"Galaxy Digital Research","relevance":"The definitive market-sizing report on crypto lending (CeFi + DeFi) showing DeFi's rise to ~67% market share and $41B in open borrows by Q3 2025, providing the TAM context and competitive landscape data essential for evaluating Morpho's growth trajectory and market positioning against Aave."},{"title":"Aave V4 Overview: Hub & Spoke Architecture Documentation","url":"https://aave.com/docs/aave-v4","source":"Aave Protocol Documentation","relevance":"Aave V4's new Hub & Spoke architecture with unified liquidity and modular Spokes represents the primary competitive threat to Morpho Blue's isolated-market model; understanding how Aave is converging toward modular lending is critical to assessing whether Morpho's architectural differentiation will endure."},{"title":"Formally Verifying Morpho Blue with Certora","url":"https://morpho.mirror.xyz/pk_jXDlq-pv8TcHeN7X4-zZcYa7TLRmgv87UBCjG4i8","source":"Morpho (Mirror.xyz)","relevance":"This deep-dive into Morpho Blue's formal verification process using Certora Prover—covering market independence invariants, reentrancy protection, and arithmetic rounding proofs—is essential for assessing the protocol's smart contract security posture, which underpins the safety of over $10B in deposits."},{"title":"MiCA Regulation Explained: A Guide To EU Crypto Compliance","url":"https://www.cyfrin.io/blog/mica-regulation-explained-a-guide-to-eu-crypto-compliance","source":"Cyfrin","relevance":"As a Paris-based protocol governed by a French non-profit, Morpho operates at the epicenter of EU MiCA enforcement; this guide details how DeFi protocols with identifiable operators may fall under MiCA, the emerging DeFi-specific regulation planned for 2026, and the compliance costs that could materially impact Morpho's operational model."}]	t	Tier 2	MORPHO	0x58D97B57BB95320F9a05dC918Aef65434969c2B2	et