a21e42fd-647e-4be2-a9fe-5ef31806ec97	Delphi Digital	Independent research, consulting, and venture firm providing institutional-grade analysis on the digital asset and crypto market.	Delphi Digital is a research-driven firm founded in 2018 that provides institutional-grade analysis, consulting, and investment services for the digital asset market. The company operates as a cooperative coalition of independently owned entities under the Delphi brand, including Delphi Research (founded 2018), Delphi Ventures, and Delphi Labs (established 2021 as a protocol R&D arm, later launching an accelerator program in 2023). Their research subscription product offers actionable insights on crypto markets, DeFi, tokenomics, gaming, and macro trends, serving top-tier investors, institutional teams, and builders.\n\nThe founding team — Anil Lulla, Medio Demarco, Kevin Kelly, Tom Shaughnessy, and Yan Liberman — previously worked at institutions like Deutsche Bank, Bloomberg, and Oppenheimer before transitioning to crypto. The firm has built a strong reputation through deep-dive reports that have been cited by notable industry figures including Ethereum co-founder Vitalik Buterin. Delphi Ventures operates as a venture capital arm that has made investments across the crypto ecosystem. The company has no external investors in its core research business, giving it independence in decision-making. Delphi Labs raised $13.5M in 2023 from P2P (creator of Lido) and Jump Crypto for its Web3 accelerator program. The company is headquartered in Miami Beach, FL with a fully remote team.	Crypto / Web3	Other	Seed	Delphi Labs raised $13.5M in April 2023, led by P2P (creator of Lido) with participation from Jump Crypto. The funding was for their Web3 accelerator program. The raise was Delphi's first time courting outside investments. The core Delphi Digital research business has operated without external investors, being self-funded by the founding team.	Delphi Digital competes in the institutional crypto research and analytics space. Direct competitors include Messari (crypto data analytics and research platform), Nansen (blockchain analytics), The Block (crypto media and research), Blockworks (crypto media and research), Coin Metrics (crypto data), Dune Analytics (blockchain data platform), and Kaiko (crypto market data). Delphi differentiates through its integrated research + consulting + ventures model, deep-dive reports with actionable trading insights, exclusive community access, and strong reputation for tokenomics advisory. Unlike pure data platforms, Delphi combines qualitative research with macro analysis and has deep protocol-level consulting relationships.	https://x.com/ashwathbk	discovered	{"Crypto Research","Digital Assets",Tokenomics,DeFi,"Web3 Consulting"}	\N	2026-03-06 07:12:42.072316	https://delphidigital.io		https://x.com/Delphi_Digital	https://www.linkedin.com/company/delphi-digital	1e9bf641-c93c-4629-906a-f50db9050164	\N	0	\N	\N	\N	f	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
d847ed3e-e67f-44a7-9c65-5d8dd5c34b0d	Freeport Markets	AI-powered tradable news feed that turns social media signals into actionable trades across crypto, stocks, and pre-IPO equities via a self-custodial DeFi interface.	Freeport Markets is building an internet-native investing platform that translates real-time social media and news signals into executable trade ideas. The platform uses AI analysts to track breaking news across Twitter, financial media, and social platforms, distilling what matters into actionable trade cards with evidence and context. Users can follow trusted investors, analysts, and publications, and the AI filters noise to surface only trading-relevant signals across 400+ stocks, crypto assets, and pre-IPO names like SpaceX, OpenAI, Anthropic, and Anduril.\n\nThe platform operates on a self-custodial model where assets stay in the user's wallet with no rehypothecation or lock-ins. Freeport integrates multiple DeFi protocols into one interface, offering cross-chain swaps, yield opportunities, lending, staking, and diversified portfolio construction using a quantitative factor-based framework. The company applies a rigorous screening methodology to vet assets for legitimacy and liquidity, and routes trades to minimize slippage and MEV.\n\nFounded in 2025 and backed by Y Combinator (F25 batch) and Alliance DAO, the team of 3 is based in New York. They launched their mobile app (iOS and Android) in early 2026 and are expanding into perpetual DEX integrations, prediction markets, and deeper DeFi protocol coverage.	Crypto / Web3	API / Platform	Pre-seed	Pre-Seed round raised on August 1, 2025. Investors: Y Combinator and Alliance DAO. Exact amount undisclosed.	Freeport competes at the intersection of DeFi aggregation and social/narrative-driven trading. Key competitors include: Zerion (non-custodial wallet and portfolio app with DeFi discovery across chains), Zapper (portfolio tracking and DeFi discovery with execution across protocols), and Coinbase/Robinhood (centralized crypto platforms Freeport positions against on fees and yield). Freeport differentiates by combining AI-driven social media signal processing with DeFi execution — turning narrative and attention data into tradable strategies. The addition of pre-IPO equities and tokenized stocks alongside crypto is a further differentiator.	https://x.com/freeportmrkts?s=21&t=nNmmq43RV9J-8fLg3xTwXA	reaching_out	{DeFi,"AI Trading","Social Trading",Pre-IPO,Self-Custody}	\N	2026-03-20 09:34:17.851333	https://freeportmarkets.com	\N	https://x.com/freeportmrkts	https://www.linkedin.com/company/freeportmarkets	1e9bf641-c93c-4629-906a-f50db9050164	DeFi Aggregator / Social Trading	0	\N	\N	\N	f	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
534dfb28-6662-44b4-99dc-e4a5f280463b	Legend Trade	A gamified, social crypto trading arena with real-time matchmaking, copy trading, and trader reputation/ELO systems — incubated by GTE.	Legend Trade (legend.trade) is building the world's first 'Trader vs. Trader' arena, framing crypto trading as a multiplayer competitive experience. The platform allows users to get matchmade in real-time against other traders, discover top performers through rich media content, track their performance, and copy trade them directly. Incubated by GTE (The Global Token Exchange), a Paradigm-backed decentralized trading platform built on MegaETH, Legend Trade layers social and competitive mechanics on top of derivatives trading infrastructure. Features include competitive trading with social graph integration, reputation/ELO ranking systems, and a live community of traders. The product is currently coming out of stealth. Legend Trade raised a $1.5M pre-seed round on October 16, 2025 from notable crypto-native funds including Figment Capital, Big Brain Holdings, Bodhi Ventures, GTE, Kosmos Ventures, MitonC, and several angel investors. The platform positions itself at the intersection of social trading, gamification, and DeFi derivatives.	Crypto / Web3	API / Platform	Pre-seed	Pre-Seed (October 16, 2025): $1.5M raised from Figment Capital, Big Brain Holdings, Bodhi Ventures, GTE, Kosmos Ventures, MitonC, and angel investors.	Legend Trade occupies a niche at the intersection of gamified competitive trading, social trading, and DeFi derivatives. Traditional copy trading features exist on centralized exchanges like Bybit, Bitget, OKX, and BingX. Decentralized social trading platforms are nascent. Conceptual competitors include perp DEXs with social layers like Hyperliquid, copy trading protocols like dHEDGE, and CEX copy trading (Bybit, Bitget, eToro). Legend differentiates through its arena/matchmaking mechanic, ELO-style reputation system, and integration with GTE's DEX infrastructure.	htt