cda62790-cb76-4573-9997-009a560f3929	Sequence Markets	The execution layer for digital assets — smarter and faster trade execution across fragmented crypto venues.	Sequence Markets builds execution technology for digital-asset markets. Their platform improves trade routing across venues and helps institutions and active investors access better pricing, lower slippage, and more reliable execution. They operate as a fully non-custodial technology provider and integrate with existing brokers, exchanges, and custodial platforms.\n\nThe company addresses the critical problem of liquidity fragmentation in crypto markets — digital asset liquidity is spread across hundreds of centralized (CEX) and decentralized (DEX) venues, forcing teams into manual venue-by-venue workflows with zero visibility into execution quality, resulting in inconsistent fills and hidden slippage.\n\nFounded in 2026 and backed by Y Combinator (W26 batch), Sequence Markets is headquartered in New York, NY with a team of 5 employees. Their website claims access to $15B+ in liquidity, and they position themselves at the intersection of institutional crypto trading and the rapidly growing tokenized asset market.	Crypto / Web3	Infrastructure	Seed	Y Combinator Winter 2026 batch. No other funding rounds publicly confirmed.	Sequence Markets operates in the digital asset execution and smart order routing space. Key competitors include: Talos (institutional crypto trading infrastructure), CoinRoutes (smart order routing for crypto), and FalconX (institutional crypto prime brokerage, though FalconX operates a principal trading/prime brokerage model which differs from Sequence Markets' non-custodial execution technology approach). Sequence Markets differentiates with its non-custodial architecture and unified CEX+DEX liquidity sourcing in a single workflow.	https://sequencemkts.com/	discovered	{"crypto execution","digital assets","trade infrastructure","tokenized assets","smart order routing"}	\N	2026-03-06 06:56