b42d2a15-8eeb-4bcd-95f2-d920edfb373b	PredictParity (Parity)	Cross-platform prediction market aggregator enabling users to trade, track top traders, and analyze market data across multiple prediction market platforms.	PredictParity, branded as Parity, is building a cross-platform prediction market aggregator that allows users to trade prediction markets across multiple venues (such as Polymarket and Kalshi), track top traders, analyze market data, and make more informed trading decisions. The platform positions itself as a unifying layer for the rapidly growing prediction markets space.\n\nThe company is in a very early pre-launch phase — its Twitter account (@PredictParity) was created in September 2025 with ~2,860 followers but has not yet posted content. The founder, known as 'MovieTime' (@MovieTimeDev), is an active voice in the prediction markets community, sharing analysis on prediction market accuracy, arbitrage opportunities between platforms like Polymarket and Kalshi, and market dynamics. The company explicitly states 'NO COIN' on its Twitter profile, distancing itself from any associated tokens.\n\nThe prediction market industry has seen significant growth, with major platforms like Kalshi and Polymarket raising at multi-billion dollar valuations. Parity appears to be positioning itself in the aggregator/tooling layer of this ecosystem.	Crypto / Web3	API / Platform	Pre-seed	\N	The prediction market aggregator/tooling space is nascent but increasingly crowded. Direct competitors in the aggregation layer include: Polynance (prediction market aggregator with SDK), pmxt (open-source SDK for Polymarket/Kalshi/Limitless, self-described as 'CCXT for prediction markets'), Oddpool (cross-venue odds aggregation and analytics, described as 'the Bloomberg for prediction markets'), TradeFox (professional prediction market aggregator and prime brokerage backed by Alliance DAO and CMT Digital), Forcazt (AI-powered prediction market analytics and aggregator), and PolyRouter (data aggregation in open beta). The major prediction market platforms — Polymarket (crypto-native, $3.7B+ election volume) and Kalshi (CFTC-regulated, $11B valuation as of December 2025) — are the primary venues Parity would aggregate across. Opinion ($20M pre-Series A from Hack VC/Jump Crypto) is another growing prediction market platform. Differentiation is unclear at this stage given the pre-launch status.	https://x.com/movietimedev?s=21&t=nNmmq43RV9J-8fLg3xTwXA	in_diligence	{"prediction markets","market aggregator","cross-platform trading",Polymarket,Kalshi}	\N	2026-03-20 09:34:44.734407	https://predictparity.com	\N	https://x.com/PredictParity	\N	1e9bf641-c93c-4629-906a-f50db9050164	Prediction Markets	2	8	The Founder (Movietimedevv) seems like he has a strong technical understanding of the prediction market ecosystem and is essentially building a UX layer on top of different pred. mkts, aided by intelligence from AI. 	\N	f	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
1b06af05-1b8d-4312-8cd4-b0de8fad4245	Covenant AI (Templar)	Decentralized AI training infrastructure on Bittensor, enabling permissionless, incentivized pre-training, post-training, and compute provisioning for large language models.	Covenant AI is building an end-to-end decentralized AI training stack on the Bittensor blockchain, consisting of three interconnected platforms (called 'orders'): Templar (Subnet 3) for permissionless decentralized pre-training of large language models, Basilica (Subnet 39) for decentralized GPU compute provisioning, and Grail (Subnet 81) for reinforcement learning-based post-training. What started as the Templar project has expanded into the broader Covenant AI ecosystem under the motto 'One Covenant, Many Orders.'\n\nThe team has trained Covenant72B — a 72-billion-parameter model on 1.2+ trillion tokens using fully permissionless, decentralized infrastructure — claimed to be the largest model ever trained in a decentralized setting. They have published two key research papers accepted at a NeurIPS workshop (OPT2025): Gauntlet (a blockchain-compatible reward mechanism for distributed training) and SparseLoCo (a communication-efficient optimizer that combines top-k sparsification with 2-bit quantization, achieving 1-3% gradient communication). Their system has demonstrated approximately 6% communication overhead.\n\nCovenant AI is transitioning from pure research to a research-plus-product model, with training/fine-tuning APIs and enterprise sales in motion. The project operates on the Bittensor network where miners contribute compute and earn TAO token rewards proportional to their verified contributions to model improvement. The team is currently developing 'Templar: Crusades,' a competition system for optimized training code implementations.	Crypto / Web3	Open Source	\N	No confirmed traditional VC funding rounds. The project operates on Bittensor's token-based incentive system (TAO emissions). Revenue model is transitioning toward paid pre-training services with plans for 100% of training fees to buy back Covenant tokens.	Covenant AI competes in the decentralized AI training space against several projects: Prime Intellect (raised $70.4M total including $15M led by Founders Fund, trained INTELLECT-3 106B MoE model, though that run used centralized GPUs), Nous Research ($50M Series A led by Paradigm at $1B token valuation, building decentralized training on Solana), Gensyn (verifiable training computation), and Pluralis.ai (SWARM parallelism approaches). Additionally, Bittensor-native competitors like IOTA subnet pursue similar decentralized training goals. Covenant differentiates through being the only fully permissionless, live production system for decentralized training at scale on Bittensor, with novel algorithms (SparseLoCo, Gauntlet) and a vertically integrated stack covering pre-training, compute, and post-training.	https://x.com/tplr_ai	discovered	{"Decentralized AI","Distributed Training",Bittensor,"LLM Pre-training","Open Source AI"}	\N	2026-03-20 09:34:06.13532	https://tplr.ai	https://github.com/tplr-ai	https://x.com/tplr_ai	\N	1e9bf641-c93c-4629-906a-f50db9050164	Decentralized AI Infrastructure	0	9	Ran a 72B param training run in a decentralized manner, with commodity internet. Runs 3 subnets on bittensor with liquid tokens. ~150m combined mcap of subnet tokens. SN3 is most interesting. 	\N	f	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
1856f2b2-f134-4455-9a94-d8ae2f4a1f41	Splits Protocols, Inc.	Financial infrastructure for onchain teams — audited, open-source smart contracts for splitting, distributing, and managing onchain payments across EVM chains.	Splits Protocols (branded as Splits, formerly 0xSplits) builds the financial infrastructure layer for onchain teams. Their core product is a set of audited, open-source, non-upgradeable smart contracts that enable trustless, composable, gas-efficient splitting and distribution of ETH and ERC20 tokens. The protocol charges zero fees on every transaction. Key contract primitives include Split (percentage-based revenue distribution), Waterfall (sequential/tiered payouts for expense recoupment), Swapper (automatic token conversion), and Liquid Splits (NFT-represented transferable ownership). The protocol has been integrated into major web3 platforms including SuperRare, 1stDibs, Sound, Zora, Art Blocks, and Arpeggi Labs, and powers Protocol Guild's distribution of donations to Ethereum core developers.\n\nMore recently, Splits has expanded from payment primitives into a full-stack financial operations platform with 'Teams' — a multichain multisig system with passkey-based access control for managing team funds and onchain operations via smart contract wallets. Teams offers crosschain multi-signature accounts with professional workflows for treasury management. The company provides a comprehensive developer toolkit including SDK, subgraph, prebuilt UI components (SplitsKit), and API, positioning itself as both protocol infrastructure and an application layer for onchain business operations.\n\nHeadquartered in San Francisco, Splits operates as permanent public infrastructure — the core contracts charge zero fees and are designed to run forever without dependencies. The company appears to be exploring monetization through its Teams product, which offers a more full-featured experience for onchain organizations.	Crypto / Web3	Open Source		The company is private and based in San Francisco. Crunchbase lists funding milestones but specific amounts, dates, and investors are not publicly confirmed.	Splits operates in the onchain payments and treasury management space. Key competitors and adjacent protocols include: (1) Superfluid — real-time token streaming protocol focused on continuous money flows and recurring payments; (2) Sablier — time-locked token streaming for vesting and grant disbursements; (3) LlamaPay — lightweight multi-chain streaming protocol focused on DAO payroll; (4) Gnosis Safe / Safe — the dominant multi-sig treasury management tool that Splits' Teams product competes with; (5) Coinshift — DAO treasury management platform. Splits differentiates through its composable, zero-fee, non-upgradeable contract architecture that serves as permanent infrastructure ('hyperstructure'). While competitors focus primarily on streaming/vesting, Splits uniquely addresses percentage-based income splitting and tiered waterfall distributions.	https://x.com/0xSplits	discovered	{"Onchain Payments","Treasury Management","Smart Contracts","Ethereum Infrastructure","Open Source"}	\N	2026-03-20 14:43:15.002332	https://splits.org	https://github.com/0xSplits	https://x.com/0xSplits		1e9bf641-c93c-4629-906a-f50db9050164	Payments	0	\N	\N	\N	f	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
c093f41d-ae81-45dd-98f5-94641ff1a725	Pods Finance (Deframe by Pods)	API infrastructure that enables neobanks, wallets, and exchanges to integrate DeFi yield, cross-chain swaps, and crypto-backed loans into their platforms with minimal development effort.	Pods Finance, now operating as Deframe by Pods, is a Brazilian-founded DeFi infrastructure company that started in 2020 as a decentralized non-custodial options protocol on Ethereum. The company originally built an Options AMM allowing users to create, buy, and sell options on-chain, along with structured products like the stETH Volatility Vault (stETHvv). The company has pivoted to a B2B API/infrastructure play under the Deframe brand, providing a unified, non-custodial API and embeddable widget that enables custodians, wallets, exchanges, fintechs, and banks to integrate DeFi functionalities — including swaps, crypto-backed loans, savings/yield accounts, and lending/borrowing — directly into their own applications. Deframe's architecture interfaces with on-chain protocols trustlessly, and the platform also offers a KYC-compliant lending pool option for regulated platforms. Based in São Paulo, Brazil, Pods has raised $12.1M across multiple rounds and has been part of the FENASBAC Next 2023 acceleration program, partnering with Núclea and Mercado Bitcoin. The company also contributed to Brazil's DREX (digital real) initiative using the Starlight ZK-privacy solution, an open-source tool originally developed by Ernst & Young. Their current go-to-market focuses on serving neobanks in Latin America and globally, offering embedded DeFi capabilities.	Crypto / Web3	API / Platform	Seed	Pre-Seed (August 2020): $800K — investors include Boost VC, Framework Ventures, P2P Capital, BitScale, Zeeprime, The LAO. Seed (December 2022): $5.6M — investors include IOSG Ventures, Tomahawk VC, Republic, Framework Ventures, 4RC. Additional investors across rounds include Alexia Ventures, Arche Fund, Cyber.Fund, Daedalus Angels, Hash#CIB, 